title: Dodgers' Ethier yells at Mattingly in dugout
text:
Alex Gallardo Dodgers' Ethier yells at Mattingly in dugout 
Los Angeles Dodgers right fielder Andre Ethier catches a ball hit by the New York Mets' Michael Conforto during the second inning in Game 5 of baseball's National League Division Series Thursday, Oct. 15, 2015, in Los Angeles. (AP Photo/Alex Gallardo) Lenny Ignelzi Dodgers' Ethier yells at Mattingly in dugout 
Los Angeles Dodgers manager Don Mattingly, left, and New York Mets manager Terry Collins, right, talk during batting practice before the Los Angeles Dodgers play the New York Mets in Game 5 of baseball's National League Division Series Thursday, Oct. 15, 2015, in Los Angeles. (AP Photo/Lenny Ignelzi) Posted: Friday, October 16, 2015 1:01 am | Updated: 3:02 am, Fri Oct 16, 2015. 
LOS ANGELES (AP) — Los Angeles Dodgers right fielder Andre Ethier shouted at manager Don Mattingly in the bottom of the third inning of Game 5 of the NL Division Series on Thursday night.
